===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}

{{liushu|p}} – a tall building. Compare {{zh-l|*京}}, which however is not a Kangxi radical.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=髙,皋-“tall”,𦕺,𠆪}}
Possibly from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*m/s-gaw||t=head}}. Compare with {{cog|my|ခေါင်း|t=head}}. However, {{och-l|元|head}} instead is more likely to be related to this Proto-Sino-Tibetan root given its significant semantic agreement ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Likely allofams are {{och-l|喬|tall|id=2}}, and perhaps {{och-l|浩|vast|id=1}} (although the vowels do not agree).

